points for mapping the stretches of sequentially connected\nHSQC cross peaks on to the primary sequence for assigning the resonances\nsequence specifically. Overall, the standalone method presented here will be an\nimportant backbone assignment tool for structural and functional proteomics,\nprotein folding, and drug discovery research programs by NMR.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Feb 2013 05:05:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-05"}
